Running a Home Assistant Operating System [HAOS] VM in VirtualBox
What is Home Assistant Operating System [HAOS]?
[Home Assistant Operating System is a] minimal Operating System optimized to power Home Assistant. It comes with Supervisor to manage Home Assistant Core and Add-on. -https://www.home-assistant.io/installation/
Open a web browser and download the Home Assistant Operating System .vdi Download
Extract the downloaded .zip file
Launch VirtualBox
Create a New VM by selecting Machine > New
Name: HAOS
Machine Folder: C:\VMs
Type: Linux
Version: Other Linux (64-bit)
Memory Size: 2048 MB
Hard disk: Use an existing virtual hard disk now

Click the folder icon > Browse to and select the extracted HAOS .vdi file
Click Create
Select the VM and Click Settings
Select System
Check the Enable EFI checkbox
On the Processor tab, give the VM at least 2 processors
Select Display
Slide the Video Memory to 128 MB
Select Network
Set the attached to dropdown to Bridged Adapter
Select Audio
Set the Audio Controller dropdown to Intel HD Audio
Click OK
Make sure the HAOS VM is selected and click Start > Normal
Welcome to Home Assistant Operating System
Open a web browser and navigate to http://DNSorIP:8123
Enter a Name, Username and Password to create a Home Assistant user account > Click Create Account
Enter a Name for this Home Assistant installation (ie Home)
Click Detect to set the installation geolocation
Verify the Unit System and Currency > Click Next
Select any anonymous data to share with the Home Assistant development team > Click Next
Click Finish
